cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI, cs.CV 

The paper deals with machine learning and deep learning algorithms, specifically addressing the problem of overfitting and small data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the application of these algorithms to bioinformatics and experimental data, which suggests the possibility of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as potential sub-categories.
